  2) SUBTRACT the second from the first: the left side becomes sin(x - y) — set it equal
     to the difference of the right-hand sides;
  3) solve each simplest equation; use DIFFERENT integer counters for the two families
     of roots (e.g. n for x + y and k for x - y) — reusing one letter is a gross error;
  4) solve the linear system: add the two results to get 2x, subtract to get 2y. When
